/* 07_cascade.sql.in — compiled cascade traversal SRF.
 *
 * Per ADR 0035 + RULES.md R19: cascade is a single SQL-call surface
 * implemented as a set-returning C function. The C/C++ engine owns
 * the frontier queue, visited set, A* heuristic, tier transitions,
 * arena-aware effective-score ranking, and honest abstention.
 *
 * NOT a recursive CTE. NOT app-layer SELECT loop. NOT cursor-driven.
 *
 * Real wrapper lands Chunk 5+. The C-side astar_query_t state machine
 * lives in engine/core/include/laplace/core/astar.h (stub today). */

